President Biden held a meeting with representatives from the House and the Senate, specifically the Congressional Hispanic Caucus (CHC). The President expressed his gratitude to the Caucus for attending and discussed various issues on the agenda, including the American Rescue Plan and COVID-19. He emphasized the importance of the success of Hispanic families for the overall success of America. The President highlighted the growing Latino population in the country and the need to invest in their future. The meeting also covered topics such as immigration and the President's Jobs Plan. President Biden emphasized the importance of creating job opportunities in neighborhoods and supporting local businesses. He expressed his intention to sell the Caucus on the aspects of his Jobs bill and discussed strategy with them. The President briefly mentioned his conversation with George Floyd's family, expressing his sympathy and support for them. He mentioned that the family is calling for peace and tranquility regardless of the verdict in the trial.